                    <m:mtext fontstyle="italic">EER</m:mtext>
                    <m:mtext>s</m:mtext>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mstyle>
              </m:mrow>
            
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital "EER"} {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math> ranging from 6 to 12. Although not the same as the <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mstyle><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">COP</m:mtext><m:mtext>s</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital "COP"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> just described, these <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mstyle>
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mtext fontstyle="italic">EER</m:mtext>
                    <m:mtext>s</m:mtext>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mstyle>
              </m:mrow>
            
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital "EER"} {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math> are good for comparison purposes—the greater the <m:math>
        <m:semantics>
          <m:mrow>
            
              <m:mrow>
                <m:mstyle fontstyle="italic">
                  <m:mrow>
                    <m:mtext>EER</m:mtext>
                  </m:mrow>
                </m:mstyle>
              </m:mrow>
            
            <m:mrow/>
          </m:mrow>
          <m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital "EER"} {}</m:annotation>
        </m:semantics>
      </m:math>, the cheaper an air conditioner is to operate (but the higher its purchase price is likely to be).</para><para xmlns:q="http://cnx.rice.edu/qml/1.0" id="eip-492">The <m:math>
    <m:semantics>
     <m:mrow>
      <m:mrow>
       <m:mstyle mathvariant="italic">
        <m:mrow>
