      <exercise id="fs-id1169737780157" type="problems-exercises"><problem id="fs-id1169737780161">  
      <para id="import-auto-id1169737998747">Show that the coefficients of performance of refrigerators and heat pumps are related by <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mstyle><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">COP</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>ref</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mo stretchy="false">=</m:mo><m:mrow><m:mstyle><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">COP</m:mtext><m:mrow><m:mtext>hp</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow></m:mstyle><m:mo stretchy="false">−</m:mo><m:mn>1</m:mn></m:mrow></m:mrow></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital "COP" rSub { size 8{"ref"} } = ital "COP" rSub { size 8{"hp"} } -1} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>.</para>
    <para id="import-auto-id1169737805919">Start with the definitions of the <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mstyle><m:mrow><m:mtext fontstyle="italic">COP</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:mstyle></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{ ital "COP"} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math> s and the conservation of energy relationship between <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>Q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>h</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{Q rSub { size 8{h} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:msub><m:mi>Q</m:mi><m:mrow><m:mtext>c</m:mtext></m:mrow></m:msub></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{Q rSub { size 8{c} } } {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math>, and <m:math><m:semantics><m:mrow><m:mrow><m:mi>W</m:mi></m:mrow><m:mrow/></m:mrow><m:annotation encoding="StarMath 5.0"> size 12{W} {}</m:annotation></m:semantics></m:math><emphasis effect="italics">.</emphasis></para>
        </problem></exercise>
      
