  <glossary>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1169738035459"><term>heat pump</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169737812802"> a machine that generates heat transfer from cold to hot</meaning></definition>
    <definition id="import-auto-id1169737796495"><term>coefficient of performance</term> <meaning id="fs-id1169736619350">for a heat pump, it is the ratio of heat transfer at the output (the hot reservoir) to the work supplied; for a refrigerator or air conditioner, it is the ratio of heat transfer from the cold reservoir to the work supplied</meaning></definition>
  </glossary>
